<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-US">

<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>schizo.land</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
    <script src="/script.js"></script>
</head>

<body>
    <h3>schizo.land</h3>
    <p>write a post. if it is approved, it will show up later.</p>
    <form action="/post" method="post">
        <textarea name="post"></textarea><br>
        <input type="submit" value="Submit post for review">
    </form>
    <p>
        you can avoid requiring approval by registering an account and becoming a trusted user.
        this privilege can be revoked, however.
        an account will also allow you to (optionally) have a username.
    </p>
    <form action="/register" method="post" id="register-form">
        <legend>user registration</legend>
        <label for="register-username">username:</label><br>
        <input type="text" name="username" id="register-username" size="16"><br>
        <label for="register-password">password:</label><br>
        <input type="password" name="password" id="register-password"><br>
        <label for="register-password-confirmation">password (again):</label><br>
        <input type="password" name="password_confirmation" id="register-password-confirmation"><br>
        <input type="submit" value="Register account">
    </form>
    <p>if you already have an account, log in:</p>
    <form action="/login" method="post" id="login-form">
        <legend>user login</legend>
        <label for="login-username">username:</label><br>
        <input type="text" name="username" id="login-username" size="16"><br>
        <label for="login-password">password:</label><br>
        <input type="password" name="password" id="login-password"><br>
        <input type="submit" value="Log in">
    </form>
